d, United Kingdom","Bolyn, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Fitton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (mainly Lancashire):","from Middle English <i>fiton</i>, <i>fittin</i> ‘lie, falsehood’, for a lier or cheat.","possibly a habitational name from Fitton Hall in Leverington, Cambridgeshire, named in Anglo-Scandinavian as ‘settlement by the meadow-land’, from Old English <i>tūn</i> + Old Norse <i>fit</i>, a term denoting grassland on the bank of a river."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Hammon","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Middlesex and Ken): variant of   Hammond  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Hammond","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): from the Middle English, Old French personal name <i>Ha(i)mon</i>, the oblique case form of the ancient Germanic <i>Ha(i)mo</i>, a short form of various compound names beginning with <i>haim</i> ‘home’. It frequently developed excrescent <i>-d</i>, giving <i>Hamond</i>, <i>Haimund</i>, and <i>Hawmond</i>. Alternatively, the name could derive from the Middle English personal name <i>Hamund</i> (Old Norse <i>Hámundr</i>, composed of the elements <i>hár</i> ‘high’ + <i>mund</i> ‘protection’), which may have been used in Normandy and in 12th-century eastern England, but the former explanation is more likely. The surname was sometimes confused with   Almond   and   Ammon  .","English: in the Bradford area of Yorkshire, the name is a shortened form of <b>Ormondroyd</b>, formerly <i>Hamondesrode</i>, from a lost place in Birstall (Yorkshire), named with the Middle English (Old French) personal name <i>Hamon</i> (1 above) + Middle English <i>roid</i>, a southern Yorkshire pronunciation of Old English <i>rod</i> ‘clearing’.","Irish: generally an importation from England, but occasionally an adopted name for <b>Mac Ámoinn</b>, see   McCammon  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Hammon Fitton was born in 1324, in Cheshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Richard Fitton, was 30 and his mother, Joan de Legh, was 19. He married Elizabeth THORNTON in 1345, in Dutton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. He died in 1374, in his hometown, at the age of 50."},"et":{"1324–1374":"1324–1374","1328–1365":"1328–1365","1345–1382":"1345–1382","1347–Male":"1347–Surnud","1348–Female":"1348–Surnud","1294–1371":"1294–1371","1305–1379":"1305–1379","1374":"1374","ABT 1347":"umbes 1347","1371":"1371","1294":"1294","1382":"1382","1305":"1305","1348":"1348","1347":"1347","1324":"1324","1379":"1379","1345":"1345","BEF 1365":"enne 1365","1365":"1365","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","Dutton, Cheshire, England":"Dutton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Le Boleyn, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Boleyn, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Bolyn, Cheshire, ENGLAND":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bolyn, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1324–1374":"1324–1374","1328–1365":"1328–1365","1345–1382":"1345–1382","1347–Male":"1347–Kuollut","1348–Female":"1348–Kuollut","1294–1371":"1294–1371","1305–1379":"1305–1379","1374":"1374","ABT 1347":"noin 1347","1371":"1371","1294":"1294","1382":"1382","1305":"1305","1348":"1348","1347":"1347","1324":"1324","1379":"1379","1345":"1345","BEF 1365":"ennen vuotta 1365","1365":"1365","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","Dutton, Cheshire, England":"Dutton, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Le Boleyn, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Boleyn, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Bolyn, Cheshire, ENGLAND":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bolyn, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1324–1374":"1324–1374","1328–1365":